>Finally, there&#8217;s the social dynamic of &#8220;blue checks&#8221; &#8=
212; verified accounts. For a long time, Twitter paused verification for al=
most everyone, so the blue checkmarks became an artificially scarce commodi=
ty. And though blue checks are nearly useless in terms of actual Twitter fu=
nctionality, their artificial scarcity creates a status difference between =
those who have them and those who don&#8217;t. And that leads to a sort of =
class consciousness on Twitter &#8212; a resentment of &#8220;bluechecks&#8=
221;, and a characterization of them as aloof, self-important, and shallow.=
